1
00:00:00,300 --> 00:00:04,000
StellarFund — cross-border crowdfunding, live on Stellar mainnet.

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:08,000
First, connect a Stellar wallet — this is real XLM on mainnet.

3
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:14,000
Open a campaign to see its milestone timeline and progress.

4
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:20,000
Contribute real XLM — held in a smart-contract escrow, not by a middleman.

5
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:26,000
Approve the transaction; funds release only as milestones are met.

6
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:32,000
The contribution is confirmed on-chain in seconds.

7
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:36,000
Every transaction is public and verifiable on stellar.expert.

8
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:41,000
Browse campaigns across categories — Education, Health, Technology and more.

9
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:46,000
Search and filters make it easy to find a cause to support.

10
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:52,000
Now let's create a brand-new campaign, live on mainnet.

11
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:59,000
Give it an identity: title, description, category and a cover image.

12
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:06,000
Set the funding goal in XLM.

13
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:14,000
Define the milestones — each releases one tranche of funds as it's met.

14
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:22,000
The milestones must sum to the goal; this is enforced on-chain.

15
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:30,000
Submitting deploys a dedicated escrow contract through the Factory.

16
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:37,000
Sign the transaction in your wallet to confirm.

17
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:45,000
In seconds, the new campaign is live on-chain.

18
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:50,000
Here's the campaign we just created, now live on the home page.

19
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:55,000
The Proof of Users board reads real backers straight from the blockchain.

20
00:01:55,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Every wallet and amount is verifiable on stellar.expert — no fake numbers.

21
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:08,000
We collect user details and feedback through a short form.

22
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:18,000
Name, email and wallet address — so each response is verifiable on-chain.

23
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:28,000
Users rate the experience and how easy it was to contribute.

24
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:38,000
They tell us what they did: connect, contribute, or create a campaign.

25
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:50,000
And what they liked most, plus what we should build next.

26
00:02:50,000 --> 00:03:02,000
This feedback drives the roadmap — TTL hardening, fee sponsorship, profiles.

27
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:14,000
Real users, real transactions, real feedback — all on Stellar mainnet.

28
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:22,000
StellarFund — global funding, milestone-enforced. Thanks for watching!
